  "text": "## TypeScript Module Resolution Implementation\n\nThe TypeScript compiler implements a comprehensive module resolution system located primarily in **src/compiler/moduleNameResolver.ts**, with supporting utilities in **src/compiler/utilities.ts** and **src/compiler/moduleSpecifiers.ts**.\n\n### Main Entry Point\n\nThe **resolveModuleName** function (line 1401) serves as the primary entry point for all module resolution. It dispatches to different resolution strategies based on the moduleResolution compiler option:\n- **Node16** via node16ModuleNameResolver (line 1704)\n- **NodeNext** via nodeNextModuleNameResolver (line 1717)  \n- **Node10** via nodeModuleNameResolver (line 1770)\n- **Classic** via classicNameResolver (line 3250)\n- **Bundler** via bundlerModuleNameResolver (line 1761)\n\n### Strategy Implementation\n\nBoth Node16 and NodeNext strategies delegate to **nodeNextModuleNameResolverWorker** (line 1730), which sets appropriate feature flags (NodeResolutionFeatures enum at line 1682) and calls the core **nodeModuleNameResolverWorker** (line 1795).\n\nThe nodeModuleNameResolverWorker maintains a **ModuleResolutionState** object (line 318) that carries:\n- Compiler options and resolution host\n- PackageJsonInfoCache for caching\n- NodeResolutionFeatures flags (Exports, EsmMode, ExportsPatternTrailers)\n- Resolution conditions (ESM/CJS determined by getConditions at line 752)\n- Diagnostic callback for failure reporting\n- traceEnabled flag for diagnostic tracing\n\n### Package.json Exports Field Resolution\n\nThe exports field resolution chain flows through:\n1. **loadModuleFromExports** (line 2613) - entry point for conditional exports\n2. **loadModuleFromExportsOrImports** (line 2702) - handles both exports and imports fields with pattern matching\n3. **getLoadModuleFromTargetExportOrImport** (line 2745) - returns a specialized recursive function that:\n   - Evaluates conditional targets based on resolution conditions (from getConditions)\n   - Applies comparePatternKeys (line 2688) to sort patterns by specificity\n   - Matches pattern trailers using matchesPatternWithTrailer for ExportsPatternTrailers feature\n   - Recursively processes arrays and nested objects\n\nThe **allKeysStartWithDot** utility (line 2567) identifies sub-mappings (exports with keys starting with '.').\n\n### Package.json Information Handling\n\nThe **getPackageJsonInfo** function (line 2440) is the central helper that:\n- Loads package.json from a directory\n- Caches results using PackageJsonInfoCache interface\n- Records failed lookups for invalidation\n- Returns PackageJsonInfo with packageDirectory and contents\n\n**getPackageScopeForPath** (line 2394) traverses ancestor directories using **forEachAncestorDirectoryStoppingAtGlobalCache** (line 3038) to locate the containing package's scope.\n\nSpecialized readers for package.json fields:\n- **readPackageJsonField** (line 358) - generic typed field reader with tracing\n- **readPackageJsonMainField** (line 403) - reads 'main' field\n- **readPackageJsonTypesFields** (line 394) - reads 'typings'/'types' fields\n- **getVersionPathsOfPackageJsonInfo** - handles typesVersions conditions\n\n### Path Mapping Support\n\nThe **tryLoadModuleUsingPaths** function (line 3158) implements path mapping (baseUrl/paths options):\n- Uses **matchPatternOrExact** from utilities.ts (line 10200) to match against parsed patterns\n- Extracts wildcard matches using matchedText/patternText utilities\n- Evaluates each substitution candidate with extension resolution\n- Integrates with the main resolution loader for candidate validation\n\n### File and Directory Loading\n\nThe resolution chain includes:\n- **loadModuleFromFile** (line 2064) - handles implicit extensions and special cases\n- **loadModuleFromFileNoImplicitExtensions** (line 2081) - explicit extension handling\n- **loadNodeModuleFromDirectory** (line 2209) - node_modules directory resolution\n- **loadNodeModuleFromDirectoryWorker** (line 2484) - reads package.json fields (main/types/exports)\n- **loadModuleFromNearestNodeModulesDirectory** (line 2984) - walks up to find modules\n- **loadFileNameFromPackageJsonField** (line 2104) - special handling for paths from package.json\n\n### Tracing and Diagnostics\n\nDiagnostic tracing is controlled by:\n- **isTraceEnabled** (line 120) - checks traceResolution compiler option\n- **trace** function (line 115) - outputs formatted diagnostic messages\n- Integrated throughout all resolution functions to log:\n  - Module lookup attempts\n  - Cache hits\n  - Pattern matches\n  - Export/import field processing\n  - Resolution failures and reasons\n\nFailures are collected in the failedLookupLocations array within ModuleResolutionState for later reporting and invalidation.\n\n### Resolution State Management\n\nThe **createModuleResolutionCache** function (line 1329) creates caches supporting:\n- Directory-based caching with resolution mode awareness\n- Non-relative module name caching\n- PackageJsonInfoCache for across-file package.json reuse\n- Readonly mode for frozen caches\n\n### Classic Resolution\n\nThe **classicNameResolver** (line 3250) implements TypeScript's original resolution algorithm:\n- No node_modules concept\n- Relative and non-relative imports resolved differently\n- Support for @types directory lookups\n- Integration with typeRoots option via resolveFromTypeRoot function\n- Still supports path mapping and baseUrl like Node resolution\n\nThe classic resolver shares infrastructure (path matching, tracing, caching) with Node resolution but uses simpler directory traversal via forEachAncestorDirectory patterns."
